12:14.607 --> 12:16.657
<b>What was that sound?</b>

12:16.657 --> 12:18.947
<b>So foolish of you to not know.</b>

12:18.947 --> 12:20.617
<b>It is the sound of a drum.</b>

12:20.617 --> 12:21.737
<b>Is there a festival?</b>

12:21.737 --> 12:25.557
<b>So, did the two of you truly not mate last night?</b>

12:27.147 --> 12:30.017
<b>Denji is surprisingly gentlemanly.</b>

12:32.037 --> 12:34.557
<b>I can't believe you put up with the ramen here.</b>

12:35.167 --> 12:36.697
<b>It's pretty disgusting.</b>

12:40.587 --> 12:41.447
<b>Who are you?</b>

12:41.837 --> 12:43.707
<b>Seems pretty tasty to me.</b>

12:43.707 --> 12:46.147
<b>Do not think you can simply speak to me!</b>

12:46.727 --> 12:49.457
<b>I suppose you can't tell what the good stuff is.</b>

12:50.127 --> 12:52.167
<b>I guess it's understandable, though.</b>

12:52.167 --> 12:57.817
<b>They say if you don't get variety in your early years,
 your palate never develops when you grow up.</b>

12:58.977 --> 13:01.557
<b>And that then reduces
 your overall sense of happiness.</b>

13:01.557 --> 13:03.667
<b>I am rather happy!</b>

13:03.667 --> 13:05.047
<b>Shall we leave?</b>

13:05.047 --> 13:07.797
<b>My grandpa was the kindest man in the world.</b>

13:08.327 --> 13:10.897
<b>He brought me to expensive places to eat good food.</b>

13:12.477 --> 13:16.597
<b>He was a member of the yakuza.
 But a virtuous one.</b>

13:17.187 --> 13:21.737
<b>I suppose people like him
 are what people call a necessary evil.</b>

13:22.457 --> 13:26.247
<b>The number of women and children he killed
 could be counted on one hand.</b>

13:26.797 --> 13:30.107
<b>He'd buy me anything I wanted
 with his drug money.</b>

13:31.467 --> 13:35.837
<b>He was a true bearer of the Tokyo spirit,
 and everyone liked him.</b>

13:38.767 --> 13:40.597
<b>Denji, you liked him too, didn't you?</b>

13:42.957 --> 13:44.977
<b>What are you trying to start here?</b>

13:44.977 --> 13:45.977
<b>Do you know him?</b>

13:46.457 --> 13:50.897
<b>The Gun Devil wants your heart.</b>

14:00.557 --> 14:01.067
<b>Topknot!</b>

14:01.507 --> 14:02.117
<b>Yip.</b>

14:20.667 --> 14:21.967
<b>Hayakawa Aki.</b>

14:22.987 --> 14:26.977
<b>You put something preposterous in my mouth.</b>

14:27.927 --> 14:30.897
<b>Neither human, nor devil.</b>

14:44.947 --> 14:47.697
<b>Power, stop Himeno's bleeding.</b>

14:48.507 --> 14:49.547
<b>A spike?</b>

14:58.627 --> 14:59.467
<b>Shoot!</b>

15:02.367 --> 15:02.967
<b>Three.</b>

15:16.287 --> 15:17.107
<b>Shoot!</b>

15:18.937 --> 15:19.687
<b>Two.</b>

15:25.827 --> 15:26.447
<b>Shoot!</b>

15:29.077 --> 15:29.657
<b>One.</b>

15:34.147 --> 15:35.957
<b>Getting tired of that weird thing.</b>

15:35.957 --> 15:37.997
<b>Finish him, Curse!</b>

15:38.897 --> 15:39.757
<b>Zero.</b>

16:08.467 --> 16:09.237
<b>How's Himeno?!</b>

16:11.087 --> 16:13.207
<b>A physician had best see to her soon.</b>

16:14.287 --> 16:15.077
<b>He...</b>

16:15.737 --> 16:17.837
<b>used a gun.</b>

16:18.267 --> 16:22.497
<b>It should be impossible to get one in Japan
 unless you're a policeman or a devil hunter.</b>

16:23.257 --> 16:27.297
<b><i>The Gun Devil wants your heart.{from a bit earlier this ep}</i></b>

16:29.387 --> 16:31.757
<b>First, we need to have Himeno treated!</b>

16:31.757 --> 16:33.217
<b>The Curse Devil.</b>

16:34.107 --> 16:37.127
<b>A certain number of stabs with its spike can kill anyone.</b>

16:37.127 --> 16:38.767
<b>Is that how it works?</b>

16:39.487 --> 16:41.707
<b>Those were some good moves back there.</b>

16:42.397 --> 16:43.527
<b>Where did you show up from?</b>

16:43.937 --> 16:45.397
<b>Are you working with that guy?</b>

17:32.907 --> 17:34.957
<b>That... hurt.</b>

17:36.147 --> 17:39.047
<b>That was your best attempt so far.</b>

17:39.047 --> 17:42.797
<b>A cornered animal tries to work their brain.</b>

17:43.357 --> 17:45.427
<b>Do more of that.</b>

17:49.407 --> 17:51.807
<b>There are two reasons you lost.</b>

17:52.487 --> 17:58.067
<b>First, Power used too much
 of her blood and got anemic.</b>

17:58.567 --> 18:02.337
<b>Second, you couldn't predict my attack.</b>

18:04.107 --> 18:07.167
<b>You did well, so let's call it a day.</b>

18:07.167 --> 18:08.707
<b>I'll go have a drink.</b>

18:11.657 --> 18:13.327
<b>Pow,</b>

18:14.257 --> 18:15.947
<b>he said we're done for the day.</b>

18:16.607 --> 18:18.337
<b>That's nice.</b>

18:28.047 --> 18:30.507
<b>Wh-What?</b>

18:33.487 --> 18:37.517
<b>A beast shouldn't trust what a hunter says.</b>

18:51.417 --> 18:58.327
<b>A contract with a strong devil
 usually has some rather brutal terms.</b>

18:58.897 --> 19:03.087
<b>Just to be clear, we're not having you do this out of malice.{TLC: This should be a question/confirmation kinda thing that's continued from the previous line. as in, "we're not forcing these brutal terms to bully you, okay?" kinda thing}</b>

19:03.557 --> 19:07.337
<b>The moment you go back to work,
 it'll be like throwing you into a lion's den.{TLC: check if idiom actually exists in English}</b>

19:08.247 --> 19:10.487
<b>You'll need a weapon you can defend yourself with.</b>

19:20.847 --> 19:24.917
<b>Devils captured alive by the Bureau
 get thrown in here.</b>

19:26.327 --> 19:28.197
<b>We'll find a weapon for you in here.</b>

19:36.407 --> 19:40.627
<b>On a completely different topic,
 was the pretty girl from yesterday your girlfriend?</b>

19:40.627 --> 19:42.967
<b>Why do you always go there?</b>

19:42.967 --> 19:43.967
<b>Drop it.</b>

19:50.217 --> 19:53.007
<b>She was my partner's younger sister.</b>

19:53.347 --> 19:56.427
<b>Oh, my. Did she give you a good punch?</b>

19:56.427 --> 19:57.517
<b>No.</b>

19:58.397 --> 20:00.267
<b>She gave me some letters.</b>

20:00.927 --> 20:02.267
<b>Letters?</b>

20:11.277 --> 20:15.787
<b>These are the letters my sister sent me.</b>

20:16.367 --> 20:19.527
<b>I thought you should read them, so I'm giving them to you.</b>

20:27.797 --> 20:30.547
I keep living a life where I might die every day.

20:27.797 --> 20:30.547
Seriously, I feel like I'm about to die all the time.

20:27.797 --> 20:30.547
I mean, the devils keep trying to kill us,

